  <!-- 5. test-sctn-alt — review boxes + CBI text-col -->
  <section class="section test-sctn test-sctn-alt">
    <div class="section-wrap">
      <div class="rvw-wrapper">
        {reviews.map((r) => (
          <div class="rvw-box">
            <p>{r.text}</p>
            <div class="rvw-bx">
              <p class="name"><span class="bold"><a href={r.url} target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">{r.name}</a></span></p>
              <span class="strs">★★★★★</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="text-col">
      <img decoding="async" src="/images/peoria-business-broker/cbi-business-people-lawyers.jpg" alt="Certified Business Intermediary for Business Sales in Peoria, AZ" width="400" height="300" class="alignnone size-full" loading="lazy" />
      <h3 class="h3-style">How A Certified Business Intermediary Can Help You With Business Sales</h3>
      <p>Selling or buying a business is a complex endeavor that requires expertise, strategic planning, and a deep understanding of the market. A Certified Business Intermediary (CBI), like Phil Reese, offers specialized knowledge and credentials that set them apart from standard brokers.</p>
      <p>CBIs are equipped to perform precise business valuations, identify qualified buyers, and navigate the nuances of deal structuring and negotiations. Their certification ensures they adhere to the highest standards of professionalism, confidentiality, and ethical conduct. With Phil’s expertise, you’ll benefit from proven techniques designed to maximize your business&#8217;s value and secure favorable terms for your sale.</p>
      <p>Choosing Phil Reese means putting your goals first. We combine knowledge, dedication, and a results-driven approach to help you succeed. Let us handle the complexities while you focus on what’s next, knowing your business is in the right hands.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 6. video-aalt-sctn — valuation video + "When Is The Right Time" -->
  <section class="section video-aalt-sctn">
    <div class="section-wrap">
      <div class="img-col">
        <div class="lyte-wrapper" style="width:853px;max-width:100%;margin:5px;">
          <lite-youtube
            videoid="75l7CluKwIg"
            title="Phil Reese CBI-Arizona Business Broker"
            style="background-image:url('/images/peoria-business-broker/yt-75l7CluKwIg.jpg');"
          >
            <a href="https://youtu.be/75l7CluKwIg" class="lite-yt-fallback" rel="nofollow">Watch this video on YouTube</a>
          </lite-youtube>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="txt-col">
        <h3 class="tc h4-style" style="margin: 30px 0 0;">When Is The Right Time To Sell Your Business In Peoria</h3>
        <h3 class="h6-style">Insights to Maximize Your Sale</h3>
        <p>Deciding when to sell your business can be challenging. Timing plays a crucial role in maximizing the value of your sale and ensuring a smooth transition. Here are some key insights to help you make the right decision:</p>
        <p><strong>Evaluate Market Conditions:</strong> The state of the economy and market trends significantly impact business valuations. It may be a perfect time to sell if the market is favorable—meaning strong demand and active buyers. Keeping an eye on local Peoria trends, such as growth in specific industries or population shifts, can provide valuable clues about the best time to act.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="title-col one-col">
        <p><strong>Know Your Business’s Financial Health:</strong> A solid financial track record boosts buyer confidence and increases your business’s appeal. If your revenue, profit margins, and cash flow are steady or growing, it could be the ideal time to put your business on the market. Buyers will pay more for a business demonstrating strong performance and potential for future success.</p>
        <p><strong>Consider Personal Readiness:</strong> Your readiness to sell is just as important as market conditions. Whether you’re planning to retire, start a new venture, or shift focus to other priorities, ensure you’re mentally and emotionally prepared for the transition. Selling a business is as much a personal decision as it is a financial one.</p>
        <p><strong>Plan for Growth Opportunities:</strong> Businesses with untapped growth potential attract more buyers. If your business is poised for expansion but you’re unable to pursue those opportunities yourself, selling can allow someone else to take it to the next level—while you reap the rewards of your hard work.</p>
        <p><strong>Consult a Business Broker Early:</strong> Working with a professional like Phil Reese early in the process can provide clarity and guidance. A broker can evaluate your business’s readiness, advise on timing, and ensure you’re fully prepared to achieve the best results.</p>
        <p>It’s important to carefully consider all these factors before selling your business, especially if you want to be well-positioned on the market and gain sales that align with your goals.</p>
